    "body": "Flags for constant-time masking rely on the values being exactly `0` or `1` rather than `0` or true (any nonzero). One function, `secp256k1_fe_cmov` [documents](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/blob/e7f7083b530a55c83ce9089a7244d2d9d67ac8b2/src/field.h#L315) and [`VERIFY_CHECK`s](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/blob/e7f7083b530a55c83ce9089a7244d2d9d67ac8b2/src/field_impl.h#L365) this, but most don't. \r\n\r\nThis updates the documentation and adds `VERIFY_CHECK`s enforcing `flag == 0 || flag == 1` for:\r\n\r\n`secp256k1_fe_storage_cmov`\r\n`secp256k1_gej_cmov`\r\n`secp256k1_ge_storage_cmov`\r\n`secp256k1_scalar_cadd_bit`\r\n`secp256k1_scalar_cond_negate`\r\n`secp256k1_scalar_cmov`\r\n`secp256k1_int_cmov`\r\n",
